{{Portuguese name|Maniçoba|de Moura}} {{Infobox actor |name = Wagner Moura |caption = Moura in 2015 |birth_name = Wagner Maniçoba de Moura |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1976|6|27|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], [[Bahia]], [[Brazil]] |alma_mater = [[Federal University of Bahia]] |occupation = Actor |years_active = 1996–present |spouse = {{marriage|Sandra Delgado|2001}} |children = 3 |image=CDH - Comissão de Direitos Humanos e Legislação Participativa (23742606876).jpg}}
'''Wagner Maniçoba de Moura''' ({{IPA-pt|ˈvaɡneɾ ˈmowɾa}}; born 27 June 1976)<ref>{{cite web | title = Biography of Wagner Moura |website=Gente Babado| url = http://gente.ig.com.br/wagnermoura/p1237852135801.html | publisher = IG | language = Portuguese | accessdate = 2011-03-13}}</ref> is a [[Brazil]]ian film, television, and stage [[actor]]. Besides being a well-established and acclaimed actor in Brazil, he has achieved widespread international fame for his portrayal of Captain (later Colonel) Roberto Nascimento, protagonist of the highly successful film ''[[Elite Squad]]'' (2007) and its sequel, ''[[Elite Squad: The Enemy Within]]'' (2010). He also gained recognition globally playing Spider in the [[sci-fi film]] ''[[Elysium (film)|Elysium]]'' (2013) and the lead role of [[Pablo Escobar]] in the [[Netflix]] series ''[[Narcos]]'' from 2015 to 2016, for which he received a [[Golden Globe]] nomination.
==Early life and education== Moura was born in [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], a city located in [[Nordeste|Northeast Region]] of Brazil, but grew up in the small town of [[Rodelas]], [[Bahia]]. His mother, Alderiva, was a housewife, and his father, José Moura, was a sergeant in the [[Brazilian Air Force]]. At the age of 13, he moved back with his family to [[Salvador, Bahia]].
He graduated in [[journalism]] at [[Federal University of Bahia]] but decided to become an actor.<ref>{{IMDb name|609944|section=bio}}</ref>
==Career== In 1997 he appeared in the film ''[[Woman on Top]]'' starring [[Penélope Cruz]].
In 2007 he played Captain Nascimento, protagonist of the [[Golden Bear (award)|Golden Bear]] winner in the 2008 [[Berlin Film Festival]], ''[[Elite Squad]]''.
During the preparation for the first ''Elite Squad'' film, Wagner and part of the cast were subject to realistic special forces training conducted by Paulo Storani, a former captain of [[Batalhão de Operações Policiais Especiais|BOPE]], the elite squad portrayed in the movie.<ref>http://veja.abril.com.br/211107/p_124.shtml</ref> During training, Storani was asked by the cast director to help "develop" Wagner's aggression for the role, which he attempted to do through repeated sessions of moral abuse.<ref>http://veja.abril.com.br/211107/p_124.shtml</ref> After several days, Storani finally got the reaction he was looking for and a little more. He reportedly made a fictional threat to Wagner's family, particularly mentioning Wagner's newborn to which the actor responded with a punch that fractured Storani's nose. "That's when Captain Nascimento was born", said Storani.<ref>http://www.estadao.com.br/noticias/impresso,ex-capitao-teve-nariz-quebrado-por-ator,55880,0.htm</ref>
In 2010, he starred in the sequel to ''Elite Squad'', ''[[Elite Squad: The Enemy Within]]''.
In 2013, he played "Spider" in the [[sci-fi film]] ''[[Elysium (film)|Elysium]]''. He starred in the [[Netflix]] [[List of original programs distributed by Netflix|original series]] ''[[Narcos]]'' as the famous drug lord [[Pablo Escobar]]. Already fluent in Portuguese and English, he learned Spanish to play the part of Escobar. Moura later reprised the role for a cameo appearance in the ''Narcos'' companion series, ''[[Narcos: Mexico]]''.
As of 2017, it is reported that Wagner is beginning his debut as director of the film ''Marighella'' based on novel ''Marighella: The Guerrilla That Burned Down the World'' about the Bahian marxist guerrilla [[Carlos Marighella]] written by journalist Mário Magalhães.<ref>http://www.o2filmes.com/noticias/en/10591/wagner-moura-no-conversa-com-bial/</ref>
===Music=== [[File:Legião Urbana com Wagner Moura.jpg|thumb|Surviving members of [[Legião Urbana]] performing a 2012 tribute show with Moura as lead vocalist. From left to right: [[Marcelo Bonfá]], Moura and [[Dado Villa-Lobos]]. To their right and partially cut out of the picture is touring bassist Rodrigo Favaro]]
Besides his acting career, Moura is a [[lyricist]] and the [[vocalist]] of a [[Musical ensemble|band]] named ''Sua Mãe'' ("Your Mum").<ref>{{cite news | title = Article about Wagner Moura in ''Hamlet'' and as vocalist of ''Sua Mãe'' (in Portuguese) | url = http://odia.terra.com.br/portal/diversaoetv/html/2009/3/wagner_moura_brega_e_chique_1575.html | publisher = [[O Dia]] | date = 2009-03-21 | accessdate = 2009-04-05}}</ref> In 2012, he guest performed as lead vocalist for some [[Legião Urbana]] tribute shows, featuring surviving members [[Marcelo Bonfá]] and [[Dado Villa-Lobos]].
==Personal life== Since 2001, Moura has been married to journalist and photographer Sandra Delgado, with whom he has three sons: Bem, Salvador, and José. He practices [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]]. Moura's native language is Portuguese, but he also fluently speaks both English and Spanish. For his portrayal of Pablo Escobar in ''Narcos'', Moura went back to college to take Spanish for foreigners, to perfect his pronunciation as someone who speaks Spanish as a first language. Moura had to gain over 40 pounds to play the role of Pablo Escobar; after production of the second season of Narcos, Moura decided to lose the weight with an all vegan diet.<ref>{{cite web|last1=De Campos Mello|first1=Raphaela|title=Meditação transcendental: a técnica de David Lynch e Wagner Moura|url=http://casa.abril.com.br/materia/meditacao-transcendental-a-tecnica-de-david-lynch-e-wagner-moura|website=Casa.com|accessdate=28 September 2014|date=July 9, 2012|quote=Assim como Lynch, praticante há 40 anos, diversos artistas aderiram ao treinamento mental, entre eles Oprah Winfrey, Clint Eastwood, Paul McCartney e o brasileiro Wagner Moura.}}</ref>
